data.title: Brian McFadden says he hasn't spoken to Westlife for more than a decade
data.meta_description: The former Westlife member hasn't spoken to his bandmates for a very long time.
data.text:
Brian McFadden hasn't spoken to any of his former Westlife bandmates for 12 years.

The 41-year-old singer suddenly quit the group in 2004 and embarked on a solo career, releasing his debut album Irish Son that same year.

Read more: Brian McFadden knocked himself out throwing a TV

His four bandmates — Shane Filan, Markus Feehily, Kian Egan and Nicky Byrne — continued to perform together until 2012 and then reformed the band without McFadden in 2018.

"The last time we were all in the same room was when I was living in LA and we went for dinner," McFadden told the Secure the Insecure podcast — reported via The Sun.

Watch: Brian McFadden once knocked himself out trying to be rock and roll

McFadden added: "I was about 28, so we haven't even spoken in about 12 years ago. The boys were in town shooting a music video.

"We went for dinner then the boys came back to my house. That was the last time the five of us were together."

Read more: Brian McFadden says Britain needs leader like Donald Trump

But despite his estrangement from Westlife, McFadden insisted that there is "no negative feeling" between him and his former bandmates.

He said: "You separate and go your own way. You think you're going to keep in touch but you don't, your lives go in different directions. That's what happened to us.

"If I saw any of the boys now I'd sit and have a pint and it'd probably be like we saw each other yesterday. There's no animosity, there's no badness, there's no negative feeling towards each other."

Since departing Westlife, McFadden has released five solo albums and competed on the 2019 series of Dancing On Ice with Alex Murphy.

Read more: McFadden reveals Westlife song he can't stand

He also formed supergroup Boyzlife with Boyzone alumnus Keith Duffy and the duo are set to unveil their second studio album later this year.

The star also became a dad for the third time last year, welcoming his first child with fiancée Danielle Parkinson.
